// lookupCache has dynamic key-value pair that auto-garbage-collects when heavyData reference is dropped`,conceptContext:"WeakMaps hold key references weakly. When an object key is dereferenced, its WeakMap cached pair automatically cleanses from system memory, preventing leaks.",description:"Write a function `cacheCompute(fn)` that implements object memoization. It should return a function wrapping `fn(obj)`. When called with an object `obj`, if `obj` exists in your internal `WeakMap`, return the cached result. Otherwise, execute `fn(obj)`, record the outcome in the WeakMap, and return the resolved result.",codeTemplate:`function cacheCompute(fn) {
