// "moments ago"`,conceptContext:"Produce human relative strings by scaling elapsed timestamp offsets and compiling descriptions according to proportional measurements representing minutes, hours, or days.",description:"Write a function `formatRelativeTime(seconds)` that accepts an integer `seconds` representing a positive elapsed time. It should return a string format as follows: if `< 60` return `'X seconds ago'`, if `< 3600` return `'Y minutes ago'`, if `< 86400` return `'Z hours ago'`, and otherwise return `'W days ago'`.",codeTemplate:`function formatRelativeTime(seconds) {
